{"type":"message","id":"58fb159e","parentId":"936a8616","timestamp":"2026-04-06T16:30:46.449Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Long ago in France, a boy named Louis lost his sight at age five.\nHe wanted to read like everyone else but couldn't feel regular books.\nAt twelve, he learned about soldiers' night writing using raised dots in the dark.\nLouis thought he could make a simpler system for blind people to read.\nHe worked hard, poking dots in paper with a special tool, trying many patterns.\nFinally, he created six dots that could make every letter - the Braille system.\nHis invention lets millions of blind people read and learn today.\nLouis shows us that even a young person can change the world with determination.\nGoodnight, sweet dreams, and remember you can do amazing things too.\n🌙🖤"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775493046448}}
